00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:33,560
 I want you to see about God's favor.

154
00:08:33,560 --> 00:08:36,920
 This verse is going to unpack two things for us, and here it is.

155
00:08:36,920 --> 00:08:40,000
 First, we're going to see that God's favor is revealed.

156
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:44,000
 Remember, we want to see God's favor.

157
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:48,440
 So, revealed, it's just a word of sight that God is showing

158
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:49,520
 his favor to us.

159
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:54,280
 God's favor is revealed in his pursuit of us.

160
00:08:54,280 --> 00:09:01,240
 In number two, God's favor is revealed in his presence with us.

161
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:04,360
 So, first, I just want you to see that God's favor is revealed

162
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:06,040
 in his pursuit of us.

163
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:07,680
 What does David say in verse 6?

164
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:11,760
 He says, "Surely."

165
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:15,240
 Surely, that word in the Hebrew, and when I say in the Hebrew,

166
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:16,080
 that's just...

167
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:20,720
 I say that simply because that's the language that the Old Testament

168
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:22,400
 was originally written in.

169
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:26,800
 So, English is a translation of the Hebrew, but if you were to go and study

170
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:33,600
 the Hebrew, that word "surely," it's the equivalent of "certainly."

171
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:37,560
 There is confident expectation in it.

172
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:42,560
 David says, "Certainly, surely, goodness and mercy," we'll get to those

173
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:51,320
 in a minute, "they shall follow me all the days of my life."

174
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:56,080
 That idea of goodness and mercy following David, if you were to go look

175
00:09:56,080 --> 00:10:03,120
 at the Hebrew about that word "follow," it's the equivalent of chasing someone

176
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:05,440
 or pursuing them.

