00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:08,320
 Like, if you were to go and read through the Old Testament and you were to look

178
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:15,560
 for all of the times that this Hebrew word is used, it is used primarily in regard

179
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:20,560
 to an enemy chasing or pursuing someone.

180
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:25,080
 So, how fitting is that that David was a guy who lived on the run for years?

181
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:26,280
 Why?

182
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:29,920
 Because he was being chased by enemies.

183
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:35,080
 And now, David is saying, "Look, even more than being chased down by someone

184
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:40,560
 who wanted to kill me, there's something else that is coming in hot behind me."

185
00:10:40,560 --> 00:10:44,400
 And it is the goodness in the mercy of God.

186
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:47,160
 That's amazing.

187
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:51,280
 David is saying that one of the ways that the favor of God has been revealed in my

188
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:57,320
 life is that God is chasing me down with his goodness and mercy.

189
00:10:57,320 --> 00:11:02,280
 And he tells us the frequency to God's pursuit of him with his goodness and

190
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:02,800
 mercy.

