 day of your life?

203
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,240
 What is the goodness of God?

204
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:08,880
 A.W. Tozer, who's a famous author and pastor who lived in the early to mid-1900s,

205
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:16,120
 he says this, "The goodness of God is the drive behind all the blessings He,"

206
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:20,600
 that's God, "He daily bestows upon us."

207
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:28,400
 So, it's awesome because A.W. Tozer is in total agreement with David because he

208
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:31,480
 says, "The goodness of God, it's the drive, it's the force,

209
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:42,120
 it's the horsepower behind all of the blessings that God daily bestows upon us."

210
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:47,760
 What's interesting is the word "goodness" that is used here is the same exact word

211
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:52,880
 that is used back in Genesis chapter 1 when God creates the heavens and the earth.

212
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:56,920
 If you were to go back and read the very first chapter of the Bible,

213
00:12:56,920 --> 00:13:02,680
 what you would see is that God slips into this rhythm of creating where He speaks

214
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:06,920
 something into existence and then He steps back, He observes it,

215
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:14,480
 and He calls it good, which means that it's perfect.

216
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:20,400
 It is perfectly designed for humans to flourish.

217
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:28,960
 That same goodness, that same creative force that was in God when He spoke the

218
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:35,440
 heavens and the earth into being, that same force is what is behind God's

219
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:36,320
 goodness in your life.

220
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:38,160
 So, I just want you to think about this.

221
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:45,600
 If there was a book that chronicled every day of your life, then according to David

222
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:52,360
 here, on every single page of your life, it would read, "And God saw all that He did

223
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:56,760
 in your life that day, and it was good."

224
00:13:56,760 --> 00:14:00,240
 God saw all the ways that He provided for you today.

225
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:04,040
 He saw all the ways that He protected you, all the ways that He led you,

226
00:14:04,040 --> 00:14:08,080
 all the ways that He comforted you and strengthened you, all the ways that He

227
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:15,680
 sustained you and even disciplined you, and behold, it was good.

228
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:18,720
 Now, this is where, guys, I'm just going to be honest with you,

229
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:22,920
 this is where we have to have an honest conversation.

230
00:14:22,920 --> 00:14:31,280
 Because the reason that people walk away from God, it really doesn't come down to

231
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:34,040
 they just stopped believing in God.

232
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:35,720
 You know what it comes down to?

233
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:41,600
 They stopped believing in the goodness of God.

234
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:42,320
 And I just want...

235
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:45,440
 I want to be very honest with you.

236
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:51,520
 I've shared in this series multiple times that 2022 was the hardest year of my life.

237
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:58,320
 And there were times during that year that I got frustrated with God, truly.

238
00:14:58,320 --> 00:15:01,440
 And there were times where I questioned God's goodness.

